Data

This data has been collected on total season statistics for teams from the Big 12, as well as the West Coast Conference.

load("Seasonstatisticscleaned.rda")

Kevin Durant Manipulation

This part of the project looks at the 2006-2007 Texas Longhorns, or Kevin Durants college team. We were tasked to find the top three players in each of the major categories in the data set. We formatted that, then created a grid arrange to show that.

teamminutes <- Seasonstatistics %>% filter(Team == "Texas Longhorns", 
    Year == "2006-2007") %>% select(Player, Minutes) %>% arrange(-Minutes) %>% 
    head(3)

p1 = ggplot(teamminutes, aes(x = reorder(Player, -Minutes), y = Minutes, 
    fill = Player, )) + geom_bar(stat = "identity") + theme(legend.position = "none")

teamrebounds <- Seasonstatistics %>% filter(Team == "Texas Longhorns",

Totals and Averages of the West Coast Conference

These graphs show the year over year Total points scored and Average points scored by player of the WCC over the years included in the data set.

newdf = Seasonstatistics %>% tbl_df(.) %>% select(2:18, 20) %>% 
    melt(., id = c("Team", "Year", "Conference")) %>% filter(Conference == 
    "West Coast") %>% group_by(Team, Year, variable) %>% summarise(sum = sum(value), 
    Mean = mean(value))


teampaletteWCC <- c("#000000", "#000099", "#990033", "#FF6633", 
    "#99CCFF", "#330099", "#99CC66", "#00CCFF", "#009900", "#999999")


ggplot(subset(newdf, variable %in% c("Points")), aes(x = Year, 
    y = sum, color = Team, group = Team)) + geom_point() + geom_line() + 
    facet_wrap(~Team, ncol = 2) + ggtitle("Total Points Scored by Team Per Year") + 
    scale_color_manual(values = teampaletteWCC)

ggplot(subset(newdf, variable %in% c("Points")), aes(x = Year, 
    y = Mean, color = Team, group = Team)) + geom_point() + geom_line() + 
    facet_wrap(~Team, ncol = 2) + ggtitle("Average Points Scored Per Player in a Season by Team") + 
    scale_color_manual(values = teampaletteWCC)

##Gonzaga Players

This graph shows significant Gonzaga players, and how many points they scored on a year by year basis while they played for the team. This allows us to compare the scoring amounts of different players over different years and eras of Gonzaga Basketball.

GonzagaPoints <- Seasonstatistics %>% filter(Team == "Gonzaga Bulldogs") %>% 
    select(Player, Points, Year) %>% arrange(Year)

ggplot(subset(GonzagaPoints, Player %in% c("Dan Dickau", "Ronny Turiaf", 
    "Adam Morrison", "Derek Raivio", "Josh Heytvelt", "Matt Bouldin", 
    "Elias Harris", "Kevin Pangos", "Robert Sacre", "Austin Daye", 
    "Kelly Olynyk", "Mike Hart", "Sam Dower", "J.P. Batista", 
    "Gary Bell Jr.")), aes(x = Year, y = Points, color = Player, 
    group = Player)) + geom_point() + geom_line() + geom_text(aes(label = Player), 
    size = 4, angle = 30) + theme(legend.position = "none")

ggplot(subset(GonzagaPoints, Player %in% c("Dan Dickau", "Ronny Turiaf", 
    "Derek Raivio", "Josh Heytvelt", "Matt Bouldin", "Elias Harris", 
    "Kevin Pangos", "Robert Sacre", "Austin Daye", "Kelly Olynyk", 
    "Mike Hart", "Sam Dower", "J.P. Batista", "Gary Bell Jr.")), 
    aes(x = Year, y = Points, color = Player, group = Player)) + 
    geom_point() + geom_line() + geom_text(aes(label = Player), 
    size = 4, angle = 30) + theme(legend.position = "none")
